   News and Events

   December 27, 2001 Department of Energy Solicits Recommendations for
   Microbial Sequencing Targets The DoE is seeking nominations of microbes
   and microbial communities as candidates for draft genomic sequencing in
   support of the DoE's Microbial Genome and the Genomes to Life Programs.
   To find out how to nominate a microbe for sequencing, click here.
   Deadline March 28, 2002.

   November 2, 2000: Microbial Marathon at Joint Genome Institute: Fifteen
   Organisms Sequenced in One Month. During the month of October,
   high-quality draft sequences of 15 bacterial genomes were produced at
   the U.S. Department of Energy's Joint Genome Institute (JGI) in Walnut
   Creek, California -- a rate of better than one genome for every one and
   a half working days.

   October 2, 2000: Microbial Month at JGI. On Monday, October 2, the
   Department of Energy's Joint Genome Institute (JGI) launched its first
   "Microbial Month," aimed at turning out high-quality draft sequences of
   fifteen different bacterial genomes before month's end.... more
   May 9, 2000: JGI Sequences "Supergerm" Genome in One Day.

